cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.SI, cs.CY 

The paper discusses the development of a semantic web search engine which involves the use of ontology-based technologies to provide accurate search results for a specific domain, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques for natural language processing, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of ontology-based technologies also involves the use of databases (cs.DB) and the paper discusses the use of RDF and SPARQL for data representation and querying. The paper also mentions the use of semantic web technologies for cyberinfrastructure development (cs.CY) and the development of domain-specific search engines (cs.SI).
